<title>|a!karaken killed by a lion</title>
<summary>A lion sits waiting for the sun to set so he can stalk people. The people lie down to sleep and the lion steals up on them and drags |a!karaken into the grove. The people name the grove &apos;|a!karaken&apos;s grove&apos; after |a!karaken who was carried there by the lion.</summary><comments>1) |han≠kass&apos;o heard this story from his mother (|xabbi-an); the dead woman&apos;s little sister, whose name |han≠kass&apos;o does not remember as they lived at his place before he was born, 2) p.7364v: on Driedoorn trees (or <i>!nabba</i>), 3) pp.7375v-7375 1/2v: (29 August)  |han≠kass&apos;o feared the grove of <i>!nabba</i> trees (|a!karaken&apos;s grove) because his grandfather had warned him that lions were lying in wait there; speaking to and escaping death from a lion, 4) This story is found in Book VIII-15</comments><date>28 August 1878 (started)</date><storypages>7364-7375 1/2</storypages><category>History (personal)</category><author>|han≠kass'o (Klein Jantje) (VIII)</author><keyword><kw>lion</kw><subkw>what |han≠kass&apos;o&apos;s grandfather told him about</subkw></keyword>
